
Overview of verb besmirch

The verb besmirch has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                       
1. (2) defame, slander, smirch, asperse, denigrate, calumniate, smear, sully, besmirch -- (charge falsely or with malicious intent; attack the good name and reputation of someone; "The journalists have defamed me!" "The article in the paper sullied my reputation")
2. (1) smirch, besmirch -- (smear so as to make dirty or stained)
